&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Flow Traders is strengthening leadership across its Product Development department and is hiring an Engineering Manager in Amsterdam. As the firm scales, the quality of engineering management has become one of the most important factors in how well our teams grow, retain talent, and deliver - and this role exists to raise that bar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engineering Managers are accountable for the planning and people side of the organisation - project deliveries, growth, performance, culture and hiring - and partner with technical leads who own architecture, technical direction, and hands-on execution. The two work in close partnership; neither succeeds without the other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be measured on the engineers you develop and the outcomes your team delivers. You will spend the large majority of your time leading people and managing delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;Own the roadmap: manage priorities, planning, and sequencing of the work in line with company goals.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Develop your engineers: own career planning, promotions, coaching, and structured, continuous performance management.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Plan and build the team: lead hiring, headcount planning, and resource allocation in line with the team&#39;s roadmap and the firm&#39;s priorities.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Cultivate a healthy team: actively manage culture, morale, and productivity, and address conflict early and constructively.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Lead with rhythm: hold regular one-on-ones, give clear and timely feedback, and invest in team building.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Translate technical and business requirements into clear delivery plans, identifying dependencies with other teams and risks up front.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Act as the liaison between Engineering, Trading, and Quant teams to design and roll out new products.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Drive delivery predictability: track progress against plan, manage risk and scope trade-offs, and report status clearly to stakeholders.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Continuously improve delivery processes and team velocity.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Ensure alignment: keep your team&#39;s work connected to organisational goals and delivery timelines, collaborating closely with Tech Leads and Staff Engineers on technical direction.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;What you need to succeed:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MailCompose&quot;&gt;Strong project management skills: experience building roadmaps, sequencing work, managing dependencies and risk, and driving delivery predictability in a fast-moving environment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;A technical background sufficient to earn the respect of the engineers you manage and to engage credibly in technical discussions.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Demonstrated experience leading, growing, and managing the performance of software engineers.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;A track record of delivering software through a team, balancing scope, quality, and timelines.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Strong people-leadership skills: coaching, feedback, conflict resolution, and building an environment in which engineers thrive.&

&lt;p&gt;Flow Traders is looking for a Quantitative Researcher to join our growing trading team in Hong Kong. This is a unique opportunity to join a leading proprietary trading firm, working alongside some of the brightest minds in the industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A successful candidate is curious and seeks to provide their quantitative expertise to our trading desks. The ideal candidate must be an expert in mathematics and statistics, have an affinity for numbers and have strong programming experience. You should have an innate desire to generate and backtest new trading ideas, with generation of alpha and automated strategies as ultimate output goals. If you have the passion to solve and code mathematical problems, while having a direct impact on the business, then this opportunity is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you will do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create new trading strategies by identifying opportunities in the market through extensive research and analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Traders and Quantitative Researchers to build, test and optimize current trading models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and analyze large financial datasets to find exploitable patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement complex quantitative models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What you need to succeed&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years of work experience within the industry with prior experience working on mid to high frequency trading strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree or higher in Econometrics, Mathematics, Physics, Statistics, Computer Science or other relevant STEM fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Python programming knowledge is a must, experience with other scientific programming language (e.g. MATLAB, C++, JAVA, R or similar) is beneficial&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills to easily manipulate large datasets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to reason logically, deliver under pressure and take ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive attitude, eager to learn, proactive and able to work in a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills to be able to communicate complex problems in an efficient manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
