&lt;p&gt;Flow Traders is looking for an Network Engineer to join our growing Technology team in Hong Kong. The ideal candidate is curious, innovative and passionate about technology This is a unique opportunity to join a leading proprietary trading firm with an entrepreneurial and innovative culture at the heart of its business. &amp;nbsp;We value quick-witted, creative minds and challenge them to make full use of their capacities. If you aim high, the sky is the limit!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this dynamic role within a fast-paced environment you are the ‘network thought-leader’, an engineer who is going to help us to build and optimize the IT infrastructure for our business requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safeguard the continuity of our trading systems infrastructure and facilitate our traders in their day-to-day activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and optimise our systems which host a wide range of applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the driving force behind innovations, ranging from realizing new links between stock markets and our network to implementing solutions that optimise system stability/performance and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve the existing network/infra/systems which also includes network orchestration and automation tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage, maintain and shape infrastructures, develop and enact contingency plans and provide secondary and tertiary support to our teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frequent contact with internal and external stakeholders (traders, data centers/colocations, third party suppliers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively lookout for ways to optimise performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What You Need to Succeed&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree or Professional Degree in Computer Science / Information Technology or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 5 years of experience in IT (support/optimization/deployments) to cover wide area networks, branch offices, cloud, multicast routing, security devices (firewalls) and wireless networks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desired experience with support electronic trading systems within capital markets firm or equivalent industry (APAC regional knowledge)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desired experience supporting environments with low latency networks, capture probes and network latency management systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of Cisco &amp;amp; Arista technologies (L1/L2/L3 switches and routers, firewalls and wireless etc.)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding the specific IT needs of our organization (low latency, high performance, redundancy and high availability) and excel at resolving issues on the fly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Unix/Linux command line and networking stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Routing protocols: BGP, OSPF, multicast routing [PIM SM/DM/SSM]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on scripting experience (Bash/Shell, Python and Salt)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network related certification (example CCNP) is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge in Cloud platform environments (AWS and GCP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Data Center and cabling standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of Project Management methodology and best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to produce quality documentation on network design, diagrams and support materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to adopt new technologies and ability to contribute as a team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Desirable knowledge:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge on switching concepts: VLAN, Spanning-tree protocol (RSTP, MSTP), Port-Channel, VRRP/HSRP, CEF, TCAM etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time synchronization protocols NTP, PTP (grandmaster, boundary clock, offset) and GPS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;TCP analysis and traffic optimization with concepts as TCP Slow-start, Dup-Acks, Retransmits, SACK, Checksum and Seq Number&lt;/li&gt;
